title: Best Control of Corruption
description: In 2023, Finland achieved a perfect score of 100 in the Control of Corruption percentile rank, indicating the highest level of control over corruption globally.

title: Universal Financial Account Ownership
description: As of 2021, 100% of older adults and those with secondary education or more in Finland have an account at a financial institution or with a mobile-money-service provider.

title: Top Rule of Law
description: Finland scored 100 in the Rule of Law percentile rank in 2023, reflecting the strongest adherence to the rule of law worldwide.

title: High Female Secondary School Enrollment
description: In 2022, Finland had a female secondary school enrollment rate of 153.24%, one of the highest globally, indicating a strong emphasis on female education.

title: Low Air Pollution Mortality Rate
description: In 2019, Finland had one of the lowest mortality rates attributed to air pollution, with 5.1 per 100,000 females and 7.4 per 100,000 population.

title: Lowest Tuberculosis Treatment Success Rate
description: In 2022, Finland had a tuberculosis treatment success rate of only 1%, indicating challenges in effectively treating the disease.

title: Lowest Child Marriage Rate
description: As of 2017, only 0.1% of women aged 20-24 in Finland were married by age 18, one of the lowest rates globally, reflecting strong child protection policies.
